{"action": "resyn", "code": "import numpy as np\nfrom typing import *\n\n(black, blue, red, green, yellow, grey, pink, orange, teal, maroon) = range(10)\n\ndef initialize_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    return output_grid\n\ndef replace_grey_with_green(output_grid: np.ndarray, i: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    If i-th colmun to the end colmun of output grid is even, replace grey element in the i-th colmun with green element.\n    \"\"\"\n    if i % 2 == 0:\n        output_grid[:, i:][output_grid[:, i:] == grey] = green\n    return output_grid\n\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = initialize_grid(input_grid)\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n        output_grid = replace_grey_with_green(output_grid, i)\n    return output_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = initialize_grid(input_grid)\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n        output_grid = replace_grey_with_green(output_grid, i)\n    return output_grid\n# same size as input\ndef initialize_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # create a copy of input grid\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = `same size as input`(input_grid)\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n        output_grid = `if i-th colmun to the end colmun of output grid is even, replace grey element in the i-th colmun with green element `(output_grid, i)\n        \n    return output_grid", "gpt_code": "import numpy as np\nfrom typing import *\n\n(black, blue, red, green, yellow, grey, pink, orange, teal, maroon) = range(10)\n\ndef initialize_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    return output_grid\n\ndef replace_grey_with_green(output_grid: np.ndarray, i: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    If i-th colmun to the end colmun of output grid